gw.api.domain

Class StateSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.domain.StateSet

  • public class StateSet
extends java.lang.Object
    Easy helper class to encapsulate a set of States, which is a commonly-used concept in PC. StateSets can be converted to and from an easy String representation. StateSets are immutable: they cannot be changed directly.

      • get

        public static StateSet get(java.lang.String stateSetExpression)
        Constructs and returns a state set from the given expression.
        Parameters:
        stateSetExpression - A comma-separated sequence of tokens, each of which may be one of the following:
        1. the code of a State typekey,
        2. the name of a predefined state set,
        3. the character "-" followed by the code of a State typekey, or
          4. the character "-" followed by the name of a predefined state set.
        In case 1, the State is added to the set. In case 2, all states in the named state set are added to the set. In case 3, the State is removed from the set. Finally, in case 4, all states in the named state set are removed from the set. Order is irrelevant: all additions are processed before all removals. For example, the expression "US50,-TX,-LA" represents all 50 US states except Texas and Louisiana.
        Returns:
        a new StateSet, or null if stateSetExpression is null or empty.
